import java.util.*;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int[] arr1 = {1, 2, 3, 4};
        int[] arr2 = {3, 4, 5, 6};

        // Store elements of first array in HashSet
        HashSet<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();

        for (int x : arr1) {
            set.add(x);
        }

        // Check elements of second array
        for (int x : arr2) {
            if (set.contains(x)) {
                System.out.println(x);
            }
        }
    }
}

ğŸ§  Logic (Short Notes)

Store first array elements in HashSet

Traverse second array

If element exists in set â†’ common element

â­ Interview Notes

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(n)

HashSet gives O(1) lookup

